      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that they say it's \"telemetry\" but that feels like a cover story. if u look at the sheer volume of data being pinged back right when the haptic drivers engage, it's way more than just \"system performance.\" it's almost like they're trying to sync the hardware to the user's physiological state. if u were designing a system to secretly collect subconscious data without people noticing, wouldn't u hide it inside a mandatory security update so nobody would dare disable it?",
